{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QuqUzDo7US2skegVU1NWTt","type":"tool_result","content":"# GitHub Issue Summary: Implement manager-api Service\n\n## Issue Title\n**Implement manager-api service #2**\n\n## Core Component Details\n- **Name:** manager-api\n- **Type:** HTTP service\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Location:** `/manager-api`\n- **Port:** 9090\n- **Working Directory:** `/Users/kajendran/.asdlc/repos/default/kaj-test-18/manager-api`\n\n## Primary Responsibilities\nThe service must provide manager-specific leave approval workflows, including:\n- Display pending leave requests from direct reports\n- Process approval workflows with optional notes and balance deductions\n- Process rejection workflows with optional notes\n- Validate manager authorization via organizational hierarchy\n- Maintain in-memory organizational hierarchy and leave state\n- Expose health monitoring endpoint\n\n## Key API Endpoints (OpenAPI 3.0)\n1. `GET /health` — Service health check\n2. `GET /manager/requests?managerId=X` — Retrieve pending requests for direct reports\n3. `POST /manager/requests/{id}/approve` — Approve with manager authorization validation\n4. `POST /manager/requests/{id}/reject` — Reject with manager authorization validation\n\n## Technical Requirements\n- **Framework:** Gorilla/mux or standard ServeMux\n- **Build:** Multi-stage Dockerfile (golang:1.21 builder, alpine runtime)\n- **Binding:** Listen on `0.0.0.0:9090` for container networking\n- **State:** In-memory data structures for hierarchy and requests\n- **Test Data:** Seed manager \"mgr1\" overseeing employees \"[emp1, emp2]\"\n- **Dependency:** Leave API via `LEAVE_API_URL` environment variable\n\n## Project Structure Requirements\n- `go.mod` with module declaration\n- `cmd/` or `main.go` entry point\n- Multi-stage `Dockerfile`\n- `workload.yaml` declaring endpoints and dependencies\n- Internal packages (`handlers/`, `services/`, `models/`)\n\n## Critical Constraints\n- All files within working directory only\n- No required environment variables (use sensible defaults)\n- Authorization validation mandatory before approvals/rejections\n- Balance deduction occurs only on approval\n- Proper HTTP status codes (200, 400, 404)\n- No local server execution; compilation checks only"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fcf02d48-c95a-4c83-9923-5c3719795ded","uuid":"cac0093b-f6a3-46d3-9063-a34253a9ec76","timestamp":"2026-04-24T09:25:21.696Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":302757,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# GitHub Issue Summary: Implement manager-api Service\n\n## Issue Title\n**Implement manager-api service #2**\n\n## Core Component Details\n- **Name:** manager-api\n- **Type:** HTTP service\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Location:** `/manager-api`\n- **Port:** 9090\n- **Working Directory:** `/Users/kajendran/.asdlc/repos/default/kaj-test-18/manager-api`\n\n## Primary Responsibilities\nThe service must provide manager-specific leave approval workflows, including:\n- Display pending leave requests from direct reports\n- Process approval workflows with optional notes and balance deductions\n- Process rejection workflows with optional notes\n- Validate manager authorization via organizational hierarchy\n- Maintain in-memory organizational hierarchy and leave state\n- Expose health monitoring endpoint\n\n## Key API Endpoints (OpenAPI 3.0)\n1. `GET /health` — Service health check\n2. `GET /manager/requests?managerId=X` — Retrieve pending requests for direct reports\n3. `POST /manager/requests/{id}/approve` — Approve with manager authorization validation\n4. `POST /manager/requests/{id}/reject` — Reject with manager authorization validation\n\n## Technical Requirements\n- **Framework:** Gorilla/mux or standard ServeMux\n- **Build:** Multi-stage Dockerfile (golang:1.21 builder, alpine runtime)\n- **Binding:** Listen on `0.0.0.0:9090` for container networking\n- **State:** In-memory data structures for hierarchy and requests\n- **Test Data:** Seed manager \"mgr1\" overseeing employees \"[emp1, emp2]\"\n- **Dependency:** Leave API via `LEAVE_API_URL` environment variable\n\n## Project Structure Requirements\n- `go.mod` with module declaration\n- `cmd/` or `main.go` entry point\n- Multi-stage `Dockerfile`\n- `workload.yaml` declaring endpoints and dependencies\n- Internal packages (`handlers/`, `services/`, `models/`)\n\n## Critical Constraints\n- All files within working directory only\n- No required environment variables (use sensible defaults)\n- Authorization validation mandatory before approvals/rejections\n- Balance deduction occurs only on approval\n- Proper HTTP status codes (200, 400, 404)\n- No local server execution; compilation checks only","durationMs":8261,"url":"https://github.com/asdlc-repos/kaj-test-18041/issues/2"}}
